# Error Handling and Logging

## Two different "error code" systems (do not mix)

| System | Source | Use |
|--------|--------|-----|
| **Review rubric** (`e05`, `b04`, …) | `docs/review-error-codes.md` | Grading — how you write C++ and handle failures |
| **Runtime codes** (`DRONE_HITS_OBSTACLE`, …) | `types::ErrorRef::code` | Per-run semantics in logs and `simulation_output.yaml` |

Never put rubric codes (`e05`) in `error_ref.code`. Never pass free-form strings where structured `ErrorRef` is expected (e05).

## Never

- Crash or call `exit()` / `abort()`.
- Defer error logging to end of run (ex1 `ErrorLogger::flushIfNeeded` at shutdown is **not** valid in ex2).
- Abort the entire composition because one scenario failed — unless startup itself is impossible (e.g. composition YAML unreadable).

## Recoverable input errors

- Apply reasonable defaults where assignment allows (same spirit as ex1).
- Log immediately to the per-run error log with structured `ErrorRef`-style info.

## Unrecoverable errors — scope matters

| Scope | Behavior |
|-------|----------|
| Single run (bad start pose, collision mid-mission) | Log immediately → `score: -1` → continue next scenario |
| Group (bad `.npy` for one simulation config) | Log → `-1` for all runs in that group → continue other groups |
| Whole program (composition file missing/unparseable) | Log → return from `main` gracefully (no `exit()`) |

No `input_errors.txt` in ex2 — use per-run `output_results/run_NNNN/error.log`.

## error.log format (agreed — see `readme.txt`)

One line per error, flushed immediately:

```
<ISO-8601 UTC> <ERROR_CODE> <user-facing message>
```

## YAML error reporting

Emit **`mission_results[].errors`** as a list of `{code, message}` (`ErrorRef`). Do not use rubric codes in `code`. Mirror the same codes/messages in `error.log`.

## Per-scenario failures

- Continuable error → `score: -1`, log, continue next scenario.
- Group failure (e.g. bad map file) → `-1` for all runs in that group.

## maps_comparison executable

- Success: stdout = score only (`87.4`), no extra text.
- Error: stdout `-1`, message on stderr.

## Error API (e05) and reporting

Internal APIs: pass `types::ErrorRef` or enums — not ad-hoc diagnostic strings.

```cpp
// BAD — e05: handler receives only a message
logError("file not found: " + path);

// GOOD — structured code + message; message is fine at log/YAML boundary
logError({.code = "MAP_FILE_NOT_FOUND", .message = path.string()});
```

`MissionRunResult::errors` is a `vector<ErrorRef>`. Emit the full list in `simulation_output.yaml` under `mission_results[].errors` and mirror each entry in `error.log` (see `readme.txt`).

## Test missing inputs (b06)

Always handle: missing `simulation.yaml`, missing map path, invalid composition refs.
